Adenomyosis and fertility. Adenomyosis is a frequent pathology of the uterus for women over 40. Difficult to diagnose, adenomyosis can be responsible of pelvic pain and menorrhagia. Association with infertility is a rare event and the responsibility of adenomyosis is difficult to prove. A medical treatment with LHRH agonist can be propose to improve fertility in case of patent adenomyosis.